{"questionId":"22460111","questionHtml":"<p>Find the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> for which <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>P</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempt to find <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-value&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>e.g. sketch of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>P</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>with <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-intercept indicated <strong>OR</strong> recognition that it occurs at the maximum of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></math> <strong>OR</strong> algebraic approach (requires multiplication by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></math>)</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>40</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong><em><br></em></strong><br><strong>Note:</strong> <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>40</mn><mo> </mo><mn>000</mn></mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo> </mo><mn>600</mn><mo> </mo><mn>000</mn></mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> is insufficient to award <em><strong>M1</strong></em>, this is given in the question. There must be an “attempt to find <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-value”.</p>\n<p>Award <em><strong>M1A0</strong> </em>for a coordinate pair <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>40</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>500</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22460111","referenceCode":"24M.2.AHL.TZ1.3ciii","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the value of x for which dPdx=0.","paper":"2","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"iii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.3—Differentiating polynomials, n E Z","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.6—Stationary points, local max and min","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.7—Optimisation"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}